data.text:
Troup County Population and Races

As of 2010-2014, the total population of Troup County is 68,375, which is 16.33% more than it was in 2000. The population growth rate is lower than the state average rate of 21.03% and is higher than the national average rate of 11.61%. The Troup County population density is 153.32 people per square mile, which is about the same as the state average density of 166.73 people per square mile and is higher than the national average density of 82.73 people per square mile. The most prevalent race in Troup County is white, which represent 60.77% of the total population. The average Troup County education level is lower than the state average and is lower than the national average.
